##Every time I step out of a new coronavirusdetection lab, I go through 25 steps to deactivate the level 3 shield

Weixin Guokr42

Functional introductions, science and technology, are the language we speak to the world.

In late January, at the height of the new coronavirus epidemic, I was sent by the Health Commission to Hubei with other colleagues to support the fight against the new coronavirus epidemic.

My main job is the new coronavirus nucleic acid test, that is, in the laboratory from suspected cases of samples taken, including throat swabs, nasal swabs, sputum, bronchoalveolar lavage fluid and so on.

Protect Yourself. Protect your partner

We test team, not a large number of people, a day regularly scheduled two shifts, sometimes three shifts. Each shift is about seven or eight hours long. If the test encounters a problem with the force majeure, such as a faulty instrument or the need for reagent testing, the time may be stretched to a dozen hours.

According to the schedule, I'm working the second shift today. After lunch, I arrived at the lab with my lab partner.

My partner and I went into the lab

By this time, the first shift had finished the experiment and left the lab.

Although we are colleagues, we do the same work, but I have not seen them for many days. In order to ensure biological safety, we request that, after the experiment, do not linger in the laboratory area, it is best to return to the hotel immediately, reduce unnecessary contact between personnel. It's about protecting yourself and your colleagues.

This is necessary and effective.

Of course, not to meet people will not become strange, the network does not meet people can be very close.

A Dream, a nightmare

We chat very high in the work group, someone asked me: "For you to apply for sleeping pills, take sleeping pills, how did you sleep last night? "

We have been to Hubei support for more than 40 days, wearing three-level protection, long time in the negative pressure laboratory work, breathing less freely, brain oxygen shortage, it is easy to sleep disorders. It wasn't just me who had trouble sleeping, it was other colleagues who had the same problem, so we applied for sleeping pills from our mental health team. However, the sleeping pills will not be sent to us in a box, the captain is in possession of the drug, there is a need for colleagues, the captain will be issued to each other that night's dosage, and exhorted, not to eat more.

"I slept well, " I said. "I almost took my medicine and fell asleep after a few minutes. "

Someone joked to me, "since I slept well, did you have any pleasant dreams? "

I said, "yes. "

The other side: "Dream to see love beans? "

I:"... ... Dream of the money. Money can be a good dream."

Everyone said it was a good answer.

What a dream

I said, "I had a bad dream. "

Everybody: "What? "

Me: "I dreamed that I put the extraction kit into the machine, and the machine ran half way, and it broke. ". I finally reset the device, ready to do the sample just now, sister (my partner) said she just test the sample high pressure. I woke up scared."

According to the procedure, we need to put the test samples into the refrigerator to preserve, to make sure that the test results are completely correct, before a few days after the high-pressure sterilization. If we disagree with the results, we need to take out a sample to Redo, or let the clinical re-sampling recheck.

The machine's broken. It's a nightmare. People tell me not to jinx it.

Confronting a new coronavirus in a negative pressure lab

Our Test Group, each group is 4 people: Two people into the negative pressure laboratory core area for new coronavirus nucleic acid extraction, one person for the PCR system preparation and amplification, one more person is responsible for all coordination, material preparation, sample information confirmation and so on.

Over the course of 40 days, we worked together on the NUCLEIC ACID test for the new coronavirus, and before that, we each worked on different pathogenic microbes.

Pathogen Detection | screenshot from BTV Beijing

These days, working together, we all get to know each other: to get to know each other's personalities, to get to know each other. This kind of mutual understanding and cooperation is very important for the team work, the first is to improve work efficiency, the second is to better control security risks.

We're a team, and if one of us is a pig, contaminating the lab, or infecting ourselves, then it's very easy for everyone to get infected. So, we have to make sure that everyone is taking biosecurity very seriously, and that everyone is making sure that nothing goes wrong.

Today, my partner and I (a sister with a very similar personality to mine) completed the extraction of the nucleic acid of the new coronavirus, which is the most dangerous and infectious part of the new coronavirus testing, so, that we need to do in a negative pressure lab.

A negative pressure laboratory, as its name suggests, is a laboratory where the air pressure is less than that of the outside world; because the pressure is less, the air flows only from the outside in, so the contamination in the laboratory does not spread to the outside world, to keep the outside of the lab safe.

Negative Pressure Laboratory | Guangdong Center for Disease Control

At 1:30 p.m. , my partner and I, working together, completed the level-three suit. It's a tedious process. It took about half an hour to put on when I wasn't familiar with it, but now we can do it in 10 minutes.

It's a very ritualistic process:

Change overalls, work shoes, disposable work cap, N95 mask and simple air tightness test, disposable protective clothing, wear the first layer of long latex gloves (tie up the sleeves of the protective clothing) , wear waterproof boots, wear the second layer of PE gloves (PE gloves are smooth, can help the process better and faster to take off the third layer of gloves) , wear power supply air filtration system, wear waterproof isolation clothing, wear the third layer of gloves.

So that's it. We're kind of protecting ourselves, going from the buffer room in the negative-pressure lab to the negative-pressure lab.

Wearing level 3 protection | Shanghai Center for Disease Control

Disposable protective clothing and waterproof isolation clothing are breathless materials, we are covered in them, just put on will be very hot; especially now, the temperature every day is around 20 degrees Celsius, even if the laboratory has turned on the air conditioning, i'm still sweating from the moment I get in. So, my partner and I, we didn't want to say a word to each other.

But we didn't need to talk, either. We were already so familiar that we could just glance at each other and see what they wanted.

Let's get to work!

We divided up the work and did what we needed to do quickly, she sorted out all the samples for testing, I turned on all the equipment I was going to use, and checked that the equipment was programmed correctly, and if something went wrong with the equipment, then I'd probably go crazy.

A few days ago, one of our nucleic acid extractors was completely broken when another group of colleagues used it, and before it was completely broken, I used it several times, and every time I saw it freeze, or the program was automatically wiped out, as I reset, I would lament in my heart, "can you just hold on a little longer, until the epidemic is over? "

In the end, it didn't stick. The day it broke down, a colleague in the group said, "The extractor that's been having problems is dead. It's completely unusable. "

I: "where is the end of life, this is overwork death, is an early death, poor extractor. "

There was a moment of silence for the nucleic acid extraction machine, and a moment of mourning for the next part of the experiment. There was only one extraction machine left, and to complete the day's test, it would have taken longer to stay in the negative pressure lab.

However, fortunately, our province donated a new one to come over, this is to solve our urgent problems.

The instruments are fine, OK, I began to prepare everything for use in the Biosafety cabinet, including pads soaked in disinfectant, sharps boxes, gun tips, pipettes, pens, extraction kits..

My partner and I went through the process of adding samples to the Test Kit in the Biosafety cabinet, where my partner only took the samples, and I did all the work of not touching the samples directly, including the use of pipette sampling, all recording work, reagent box on the machine.

My partner and I work in a Biosafety cabinet like the one above

Her hands were contaminated, and my hands were considered clean, so I had to alcohol disinfect them when they needed to be removed from the Biosafety cabinet, and get clean gloves and ask her to replace the third layer.

By doing so, all contamination can be contained within the Biosafety cabinet, and the rest of the lab can be kept as clean as possible.

This is very important.

Some of the samples we took were positive for the new coronavirus. Especially in early and mid February, there are many positive samples, sometimes the sample tube is broken, or the sample cap is not screwed tight leakage, will cause a great risk; in addition, when taking samples to be tested, it is easy to produce aerosol. So, we must be careful, pay attention to every detail, and form good experimental habits, let the body to remember the handling of each situation. Because long time in the negative pressure laboratory, the brain because of lack of oxygen will appear slow memory decline and so on, and the body's memory can ensure that work in an orderly and error-free.

Let your body remember how to handle each situation | screenshot from BTV Beijing

My partner and I spent about four hours in the negative pressure lab, extracting RNA from nearly 300 samples. In order to avoid the false positive caused by the contamination of nucleic acid, the PCR system, nucleic acid sampling and nucleic acid amplification were prepared in three laboratories. After my partner and I finished the extraction, my colleague in charge of nucleic acid amplification began his work.

Outside of work

My partner and I did the nucleic acid extraction, but not all of our work, and we had to clean and disinfect the negative pressure lab, and we had to autosterilize all the biological waste in the negative pressure lab.

As we left the negative pressure lab, my partner and I began the process of stripping off the level 3 protection, which is more difficult than wearing the level 3 protection, in order not to take the contamination out of the lab.

My partner and I began the process of taking off tertiary protection, which is more difficult than wearing tertiary protection

We need to spray each other with rubbing alcohol, sterilize the outermost suit, sterilize the third layer of gloves, get a new pair of gloves, and get out of the negative pressure lab, enter the first buffer room (where we help each other remove the outermost layer of waterproof isolation clothing and boot covers, which are the most polluting and require the outer side to be rolled up inside and immediately packed into a biosecurity bin Bag) and sterilize the gloves, disinfect the floor, change the third layer of gloves, enter the second buffer room, disinfect the positive pressure air supply system, disinfect the positive pressure air supply system, disinfect by hand, disinfect the disposable protective clothing alcohol, help each other to take off the disposable protective clothing, put it in a biosecurity trash bag, remove the third layer of gloves, replace the gloves, disinfect the floor and shoes, remove the N95 mask (fold the N95 mask into the third layer of gloves) , remove the hat, remove the second layer of gloves, remove the glove, remove the innermost layer of gloves, and replace the gloves with new ones, get Out of the buffer room and change into your work clothes, which are completely wet and cold.

Release of Tertiary Protection | Shanghai Center for Disease Control and Prevention

This process takes about twenty minutes.

When my partner and I went into the negative pressure chamber, there was a strong sun outside the building at noon. When we came out, it was after six o'clock in the evening, and the sun had already set on the horizon.

We often have sunny days when we go into the lab and a downpour when we come out.

In the lab, it's like the other side.

My partner and I were ready for dinner when my nucleic acid amplification colleague called me and said in pain, "I'm going crazy, I'm definitely going crazy. "

I said,"... What's wrong?"

He: "Our 7500 is out of order again. We have a board expansion to Redo. "

Up to now, our inspectors may have time off, but the equipment has been running continuously, so equipment problems, is also no way. In this case, you have to Redo it. For this kind of rework, we usually do it again on both instruments, for comparison, which takes at least three hours.

Me:"... ... ..."

It was late at night, and he was still running PCR in his lab, lamenting him.

Tomorrow, another day.

I hope this outbreak is over.

I hope this outbreak ends soon

When my partner and I went into the negative pressure chamber, there was a strong sun outside the building at noon. When we came out, it was after six o'clock in the evening, and the sun had already set on the horizon.

We often have sunny days when we go into the lab and a downpour when we come out.

In the lab, it's like the other side.

My partner and I were ready for dinner when my nucleic acid amplification colleague called me and said in pain, "I'm going crazy, I'm definitely going crazy. "

I said,"... What's wrong?"

He: "Our 7500 is out of order again. We have a board expansion to Redo. "

Up to now, our inspectors may have time off, but the equipment has been running continuously, so equipment problems, is also no way. In this case, you have to Redo it. For this kind of rework, we usually do it again on both instruments, for comparison, which takes at least three hours.

Me:"... ... ..."

It was late at night, and he was still running PCR in his lab, lamenting him.

Tomorrow, another day.

I hope this outbreak is over.
